event_title: TPLF (rebel) attacked Northern Command (Govt.)
Abiy declared a military offensive with state of emergency in Tigray
Ethiopian parliament set-up an interim government for Tigray
ENDF (Ethiopian National Defence Forces) offensive; with accusation of human rights from both sides
Mekelle, capital of Tigray, captured by Federal forces
The war continued with increasing intensity until TPLF took the upper hand and ENDF retreated from Tigray except the regions which was Western (Wolkayit) and southern Tigray
TPLF recaptured the regional capital, Mekelle
TPLF captured southern Tigray including Alamata and Korem
Kobo in Amhara region captured by TPLF
TPLF captured the town of Dessie deep in Amhara Region
TPLF captured the town Kombolcha important manufacturing hub
TPLF-OLA (Oromo Liberation Army) joint offensive reached northern Shewa, around 190 km from the federal capital, Addis Ababa; Federal Government declared 6-month state of emergency
PM Abiy went to the war front
ENDF took control of Chifra, Afar Region
ENDF took control of Shewa Robit 220 k from Addis Ababa
ENDF captured Dessie and Kombolcha

Legesse Tulu, head of Government Communication Service, announced that government forces have taken control of several towns from TPLF, including:Weldiya,Kobo,Lalibela,Hara,Robit, Sanqa, Sirinka, Hamusit, Estaysh, Ahun Tegen, Dilb, and Kul Mesk.
Ethiopian government announced  troops will not enter Tigray
Ethiopian government pardoned TPLF high ranking political prisoners
Federal Government and TPLF agreed on ceasefire to allow humanitarian aid
Resurgence of fighting TPLF captured Kobo
Ethiopia and Eritrea (without official acknoledgement) started an offensive
Sheraro was captured by Ethiopian-Eritrean forces
TPLF announced it has withdrawn from Northe Wollo Zone in Amhara
TPLF called for full mobilisation of Tigray population
Strategic town Shire fell to ENDF
ENDF captured Almata and Korem
ENDF captured Adwa and Axum
AU (African Union) announced peace talks to be held in Pretoria, South Africa
Ethiopia and TPLF announced they signed a peace agreement that includes the disarming of the TPLF
Signing ceremony of the declaration of the senior commanders on permanent cessation of hostilities agreement between the government of Ethiopia and the TPLF
